name: the end of the world by an intertemporal sublight wave
description:
They said me the world was going to be gone, so I took my rare paper and got into the thing.

This piece has its audio and image generated by an electronic experiment using LEDs and light sensitive resistors through an analog oscillator using integrated circuit CD40106. The visual aspect is setting the primal footage to a frame buffer technique into a live vj software (VDMX in my case) and using RuttEtra emulator into frame buffered footage.... OOOOHHHH god it's eye massage ˜o˜ 

You can check the primal footage on twitter


Electricity enchants me!
